metadata.name: STRANGERS #1
metadata.description:
In the hypertrophy of civilization, human has lost his original unity with nature. Today, anthropocentrism in nature management leads to the division of living things into categories of useful and harmful, total destruction of wildlife, which have no economic significance or do not contribute to the development of the economy. Person for most of his modern range is able to significantly change the “ecosystem”, causing a significant reduction or even extinction of certain species of local culture, flora and fauna, as a biocoenotic aggressor who does not adapt to the environment, but actively changes it for their own needs. Human exists as a foreign organism that refuses to coexist organically with the environment.  

Strangers 1 of 32
Poltava, Ukraine. 2020 

Created during residence  "Two roots – an artistic research - 2020". Germany, Ukraine.
